video:video.video:description: President Donald Trump told reporters as he left the White House on Friday that he was “not happy” with the way Iran talks were going so far but that he'll wait to see what happens in additional rounds of negotiations.

video:video.video:title: Trump suggests US could have ‘friendly takeover of Cuba'
video:video.video:description: President Donald Trump said Friday the U.S. could pursue a “friendly takeover of Cuba,” telling reporters Secretary of State Marco Rubio is in high-level talks with Havana.

video:video.video:title: American supercarrier leaves Greek dock for Middle East waters
video:video.video:description: The USS Gerald R. Ford, the world’s largest aircraft carrier, left an American naval base in southern Greece Thursday after a brief stopover of a few days while on its way to the Middle East.

video:video.video:title: Pentagon and Scouting America reach deal to keep ties after Hegseth's anti-DEI push.
video:video.video:description: The Pentagon has made a deal with Scouting America that Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth said Friday would maintain their century-old partnership but refocus the organization away from diversity initiatives and other “woke” policies he accused it of embracing in recent years.
